      <abstract>
        <p>NYS appeals court rules that state's stricter auto insurance requirements introduced in February by State Insurance Department can not be implemented until a court case challenging them is resolved (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>An appeals court has ruled that the state's stricter auto insurance requirements introduced in February by the State Insurance Department can not be implemented until a court case challenging them is resolved.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>An appeals court has ruled that the state's stricter auto insurance requirements introduced in February by the State Insurance Department can not be implemented until a court case challenging them is resolved.</p>
        <p>As a result of the action, on Monday by the Appellate Division of State Supreme Court in Manhattan, a person injured in an auto accident in the state again has 90 days to notify the insurance company.</p>
        <p>Joseph P. Fried (NYT)</p>
      </block>
